FBIS4-115 "drafr063_c_94005" FBIS-AFR-94-063 Daily Report 31 Mar 1994 REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA Transvaal IFP: Civil War To Follow State of Emergency Transvaal IFP: Civil War To Follow State of Emergency MB3103180794 Johannesburg SABC TV 1 Network in Afrikaans 1600 GMT 31 Mar 94 MB3103180794 Johannesburg SABC TV 1 Network Afrikaans BFN [Text] The Inkatha Freedom Party [IFP] in the Transvaal has threatened that civil war will follow the declaration of a state emergency in kwaZulu-Natal and the murder of eight hostel residents on the East Rand. The minibus taxi, in which the hostel dwellers were travelling, was ambushed near the kweSini Hostel in Katlehong and the occupants shot. According to one of the wounded, the attackers were apparently in police uniform.
